               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of a work by Naẓīrī</summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh89005046" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1377B-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Untitled collection of lyrics or ghazalīyāt in alphabetic order by the poet Muḥammad Ḥusayn Nayshāpūrī takhalluṣ Naẓīrī (d. circa 1022/1613). 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 151v): completed by Jvālā Nāth Raniyah (?) known as Mandīyah (?) at the request of Lā[lā] Lachhīrām Pandit, 25 Ṣafar in RY 5 of the Emperor Akbar Shāh, 1226/21 March 1811. 
</p>
                        <p>Intermittent pencil foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Indian taʿlīq throughout. 
</p>
                        <p>Paper dust wrapper (BEIC legal publication on Regulation X for 22 July 1817, 8 Sāvan Banglah era, 24 Sāvan 1224 faṣlī era, 9 Sāvan 1224 Vilāyatī era, 9 Sāvan 1874 samvat era, 7 Ramaz̤ān 1232 hijrī era); partial watermarks ([…] C Wise 1814, VEIC 1814); labels, torn and stained. 
</p>
                        <p>Folios unbound; stains, wormholes, cropped, paper repairs. 
</p>
                        <p>Condition fragile. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658602.0x000001 viaf_65608155">Naẓīrī</persName>
